node.text: Last night I got to chat with Michael Kay (@kayster61) during the @Yankees game about our upcoming @YesNetwork show Home Plate! Featuring star athletes such as former Yankees players Bernie Williams (@berniewilliamsofficial), David Cone (@coney3636) and several others from all the great teams on Yes Network, together we'll be highlighting the diversity of our city visiting restaurants that evoke the delicious flavors of our hometowns. If you love sports, food and NYC – this’ll be the show for you. Can’t wait for you all to tune in on the Yes Network app this fall!

node.text: Reopening @roosterharlem has been a moment we've been waiting for since the minute we closed. I can't tell you how good it feels to step into the restaurant and have it buzzing with the energy of our staff and guests. And now we're able to welcome back some of our incredible musicians such as @singharlem here, who are bringing that positive energy up another notch! Join us for this celebration of food, music and community.

node.text: I love a full-circle moment! I met Kathy in 2017 on "Celebrity Undercover Boss" where she was using her incredible culinary talents and creativity to prepare meals at a homeless shelter. She always dreamed of going to culinary school so we arranged a scholarship to Munroe College's award-winning Culinary Institute of New York. I am so proud to share that after working incredibly hard these past few years she has graduated! A huge congratulations to Kathy @1kingkathy and all of this year's grads who didn't let anything – including a global pandemic – stop them!

node.text: Not everyone who is a trailblazer in the culinary industry works in a kitchen. @Shak_Simley is a food and social activist who sees access to food as an issue of justice. As she says, "Food is my lens, but people are my focus." She really helped me recognize just how political food can be. You can learn more about her important work and check out the recipe I created in her honor in @TheRiseIsHere. #WomensMonth #MeetTheRise

node.text: Patricia (@iampatriciagnz) started working with us as a young intern through @CCAPinc, which provides culinary training for underserved teens and prepares many for potential careers in hospitality. Fast forward a couple years and she’s already a part of menu planning at @RoosterHarlem! I love that Patricia also acts as a young mentor to me by introducing the me to the latest dishes from the Dominican Republic and even telling me about what’s happening beyond food in popular culture. Click the link in bio to get a copy of @TheRiseIsHere and check out the recipe I created in her honor. #MeetTheRise #WeCookWeRise #womensmonth

node.title: Meet the Rise: Chef Patricia Gonzalez

node.text: Almira is a beloved part of the @RoosterHarlem alum family and mother of two boys who exemplifies everything I respect about a chef: dedication, focus, passion and hustle. Watching her work, I think I’m looking at the next Pig Foot Mary—the legendary Black cook and entrepreneur from the early twentieth century. Learn more about Almira and her catering company, Truly Yours Catering, on this special episode of Meet The Rise. #WomensHistoryMonth #internationalwomensday #wecookwerise @theriseishere @Chef_AnnieAS14 @tyourscatering

node.title: Meet The Rise: Chef Almira Session

node.text: On this episode of Meet The Rise I want to introduce you a @RoosterHarlem alum, Jaqueta. Born and raised in Harlem, @_chefjay_ is curious about food, fierce and super talented. Her presence in the kitchen makes everything more delicious. Now the co-owner of @_vegansoulllc_, she cooks up healthy and delicious plant-based food for the community. They are currently raising funds to purchase a kitchen space and you can show your support by donating to the Black Businesses Matter Matching Fund. Click the link in my bio for more details. #wecookwerise #BBMMF

node.text: Chef Ed Brumfield isn’t just an important leader in our restaurant family at @RoosterHarlem and @MarcusatNohuRooftop, he’s also an innovative force of nature in the culinary world at large. Chef Ed’s Mixtape Dinners, where he creates multi-course feasts based on old-school rap and R&B music, are LEGENDARY!  I was so proud to honor him in @TheRiseIsHere with a delicious Southern dish, and I loved hearing more about what has shaped his experiences as a Black chef in this episode of Meet The Rise. Please follow him at @bk.chef.ed for more! #wecookwerise

node.text:
Yesterday we celebrated Bahama's Emancipation Day at @RoosterOvertown to mark the end of slavery in 1834 and also honor the many contributions Bahamians have made to Miami. We toasted this special day with our spin on a traditional Bahamian cocktail, The Sky Juice, expertly crafted with gin, condensed milk, coconut water and lime by our bar manager @skillz_by_liz.

Also worth celebrating is our new sister restaurant @MarcusBahaMar Fish and Chop House, which celebrates local ingredients and flavors of the island, paying homage to its culture with conch salad, fritters, grouper and more. 🇧🇸

node.text: I am so excited to present this talented group of incredible New York-based chefs who are each contributing a plant-based recipe to @VogueMagazine #MetGala that reflects their unique take on modern American cuisine. Please welcome this year's #MetGalaChefs: Fariyal Abdullahi, Nasim Alikhani, Emma Bengtsson, Lazarus Lynch, Junghyun Park, Erik Ramirez, Thomas Raquel, Sophia Roe, Simone Tong, and Fabian von Hauske!
